sentences: Hermenengildo "Gildo" Mahones (June 2, 1929, New York City – April 27, 2018) was an American jazz pianist.
Hermenengildo "Gildo" Mahones (June 2, 1929, New York City – April 27, 2018) was an American jazz pianist.
Early in his career, he played with Joe Morris (1948) and Milt Jackson.
Mahones served in the Army, and then played with Lester Young from 1953 to 1956.
Later in the 1950s Mahones toured with the Jazz Modes (which included Charlie Rouse and Julius Watkins), Sonny Stitt, and Benny Green.
From 1959 to 1964 Mahones played behind Lambert, Hendricks & Ross.
